description:
Five six. Hundred twenty-eight pounds. Forty-three twenty-two thirty-six. High soft lisp. Genius level I.Q. Thats how motivational speaker Mark Herrera sums up Rosalba Fritz Martinez, bombshell, former punkette, former psychiatrist, Z movie star in this supremely sexy, constantly surprising graphic novel.

And Herrera should know, being only one of many to fall under Fritzs lithping spell others including slobbish rocker Scott The Hog and high school nerd turned obsessive bodybuilder Enrique Escobar (and thats just her husbands).

Hernandez has taken this suite of stories (including the 48-page graphic novelette High Soft Lisp), originally serialized in Luba's Comics and Stories and the second volume of Love and Rockets, and fleshed them out with a dozen brand new pages, creating an original and inventive (and very steamy) volume that, through its connections to his main character Luba (Fritz is Lubas half sister, and characters from the Luba stories pop up here), works both as a standalone graphic novel and a further exploration of Hernandezs rich world. - See more at: http://www.fantagraphics.com/browse-shop/203-artists/283-gilbert-hernandez/fantagraphics/1659-love-and-rockets-book-25-high-soft-lisp-with-free-signed-bookplate.html?vmcchk=1#sthash.HScQGRsx.dpuf

description:
It nearly didn't happen! One year after issue 23, Tim finally finishes the last issue and the final part of the current story.

  • Dead City (part 5 - final part)

Brin kills the vampires and saves the city, but he still needs to find Kerrus...but after 17 years, Brin's printed small press adventures come to an end.

Brin returns in a new Talamander series in 2013, marking 20 years for the character who began his adventures way back in Something Bizarre issue 1 in September 1993.
name: Brin (volume four) 24
